      "id": "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::duplicated_microsoft_claim_validation",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "summary": "Microsoft issuer and tenant checks are duplicated across verifier and normalizer",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "low_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/MicrosoftTokenVerifier.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/ProviderIdentityNormalizer.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`MicrosoftTokenVerifier.validateIssuer` reconstructs `https://login.microsoftonline.com/{tid}/v2.0` from the token and throws when `iss` does not match it.",
          "`ProviderIdentityNormalizer.normalizeMicrosoftClaims` repeats the same `iss`/`tid`/expected-issuer validation before it starts mapping the claims into a `NormalizedIdentity`.",
          "A reader has to reconcile the same low-level invariant in two neighboring classes instead of finding one authoritative validation point for Microsoft claim shape."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Move the shared issuer/tenant validation into one helper or keep it solely in `MicrosoftTokenVerifier`, leaving `ProviderIdentityNormalizer` focused on mapping already-validated claims into domain identity data.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "a0215024"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "kind": "issue",
