      "id": "review::.::holistic::low_level_elegance::implicit_redirect_null_contract",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "summary": "OAuth2 identity normalization hides redirect side effects behind a null sentinel",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "low_level_elegance",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/OAuth2SuccessHandler.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`onAuthenticationSuccess` calls `normalizeIdentity(authentication, oAuth2User, response)` and immediately returns when the helper yields `null`.",
          "`normalizeIdentity(...)` sends redirects on its failure paths (`?error=missing_attributes`, `?error=email_not_verified`) and then returns `null`, so the caller has to know that `null` means the HTTP response has already been committed."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Keep the redirect side effects in `onAuthenticationSuccess` and make `normalizeIdentity` either return a `NormalizedIdentity` or throw for invalid claims; that removes the implicit `null means response handled` protocol from the local control flow.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "b36008e0"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "kind": "issue",
